<TITLE> 30 training centres for skilled workers </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Apr 27 (bdnews24.com)  The government will construct 30 more institutes to train skilled manpower. The upcoming budget will see an allocation of Tk 10 billion for this purpose, the labour, expatriates' welfare and overseas employment minister said on Tuesday. Khandaker Mosharraf Hossain was speaking at the inauguration of a workshop organised by International Labour Organisation at Sonargaon Hotel. Hossain said the government was working towards safe workplaces and decent working environment. The government is preparing to create skilled manpower and send them abroad, the minister said. He suggested that better training and improved skills would also contribute to stopping workers' repression. He said the government is giving emphasis on three issues to build safe workplace development of education and health, good governance and establishment of rights, and strengthening commercial and economic development. The minister also mentioned a number of government initiatives including amendment of labour
